The administrative building Avriopoint Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
Nobody could have expected that it also houses a mini nursery school with everything they need - the walls of colours, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a playground miniature on the terrace.
Since October of last year, can make the children of employees of Arch. Design.
The company projects - architectural Arch. Design. the workshops have produced a large number of buildings in Brno, has detaÎled its business kindergarten mini-activists since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, especially the age to make children and it was important that women architects and project leaders can quickly return to work.
At the same time that down time work contracts, nursery school is a proposed bonuses to its employees by the company Arch. Design. in the context of its social program.
The builders and architects have the opportunity to combine a job taking with the care for children.
These are the employees of Arch. Design. themselves who have imagined this kindergarten and with the support of the direction they were able to obtain a staffing of the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-activists kindergarten is financed by the resources of the European Social Fund through the operational programme of human resources and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to funding allocations (up to 2.8. CZK). They were able to buy equipment and appliances and after two years to ensure a qualified staff as well as the implementation.
After the use of the staffing of funding (two years) Arch Nevatia. Design obligation after 3 years of operating the minidisks nursery school on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted a year and it is society Economy rating that has helped make the staffing request.
The care for children is provided by a qualified staff, a nurse and a teacher throughout the day mother caring for children. Children can go to kindergarten without age limit, but they have more than three anspour most.
As it is a "mini nursery school" there can be only 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who will replace.
The operation of the school is flexible depending on the needs of parents and children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although agise individual care and education, comparable to the minidisks nursery school program is for pre-school education.
The children are not only play but a quality education is also assured - the early preparation for school benches are taught English.
The class is equipped not only of toys and games imaginative but also a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a positive and friendly environment.
Parents can at any time control their child and not have the stress of a delay to seek the children in a remote school workplace parents.
Parents use their time to work in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that creates a natural relationship of loyalty between employee and employer.
Arch. Design and is among the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and who are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens the marketing of HR.
The house in bone fascinates even after 100 years. Take a look in the domestic Gaudi.
The toît looks like the back of a prehistoric saurien, the stairs to a backbone of dinosaur and balconies to fish gueules open.
This is the house $2,223,334 Battlo in Barcelona architect Antoni Gaudi.
Because of its organic forms, the house has received from the local Kulturens bone the nickname.
Organic forms, wild colors, unusual use of stones, tiles and mosaîque fragments, front re-articulate scales and everywhere present curves, that is all that is ypique for the Art Nouveau Antoni Gaudi.
The front-side façade of the house year-particularly its lines of dream, its colours and textures pleasant reminiscent nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation foot-powered thought with precision geometry, the pace and order.
In the night the façade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of colour is strengthened.
Forms is also reflected in the domestic roll and the twisting with the same extent.
The wood copy waves executives of windows, the balustrades, decorative elements of doors, the oeilleton and the slats.
The Battlo house that stands in the street merchant Eixample Passeig Gracia neighborhood's at number 43, was born of the construction of a house in 1877 of the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
Re-constructing house is made for two years and completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a rich businessman, first insisted on the scrapping of the vieile building and the construction of another new but quickly accepted the idea of Gaudi an unusual reconstruction and cheaper.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as home multiple housing was not thought by Gaudi alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on its project that are born decorations for an apartment in representation of the owner of the building and the use of the mosaîque for the facade.
For the facade has also worked for other artists and creators.
The joint work for the plans of the house Casa Battlo began with a cooperation to achieve between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of the house of Gaudi Casa Mila and Guell Park in which there are other Gaudi works.
The local have dubbed the home to gladden just after the finish because of its "Maison bone" organic forms.
Others, given the specific mechanism to open windows have called "the house that baille."
It is said that on top of the building there was a sword similar to that of St. Georges the boss of Catalonia.
Other elements of sculpture construction contain hidden religious grounds.
Gaudi was in its time a single system for the home central heating, with the aeration vents and chimneys typical.
Their angle of 45 degrees seems odd.
During the establishment Gaudi has not complied with the directives of building then and has not been hindering by them.
At the start of construction permits from the city was built, knowing, of course, that the data brought on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years after finishing the council was horrified and requested changes.
He did not like, for example, the members of the council that the pillars of the construction empiettent public on the sidewalk.
He never had to change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the appeal of the city EPP-ED's Battlo asked (and Brodec satisfaction) permission to rent the top two floors.
The owner moved to lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common lounge and the third a private room and a portion of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a 9000-.
The entire house of six floors is shared by a staircase that leads up to an independent toît terrace.
All angles and the straightaways were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and their replacement by amregates walls.
Gaudi worked the modern concept of liaison spaces.
The joint party may be linked completely by opening the doors of double-banking and high society can communicate comfortably or limit the private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi has received new facades a non-traditional toîture and two floors.
The game of Gaudi with light is also impressive, blue glass and white tiles with which is decorated the courtyard and the wells of lights.
The game in two colours gives a maximum of light in all floors of the house.
It was enough simply to bet on the principle that the white reflête more than the dark instead absorbs the sun's rays.
The Casa Battlo home that has been registered in 2005 in the World Heritage Fund UNESCO may be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the more spacious and the most beautiful apartment accessible to the public.
Owners have decided to cross it in 2002 to the 150ème anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
