The devices to follow the people are increasingly requested by parents who want to monitor their children.
The fear for their child leads them more people to think monitor through a GPS.
The system, put in place early to seek out the cars can equally well be used to trace the movement of people and help for some cases such as for example the small Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is now so large that a box of matches but will soon be the size of a show.
The case of the small Anicka moved a large number of people and they have begun to seek ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to confuse their privacy.
"We are trying to say to all that this is not principal--but but just another way to reduce the likelihood that there is another tragedy," said Petr Pilin of the company MAcro Weil is one of the suppliers of tracking devices on the Czech market.
"I confess that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet met with such cases."
"The majority of people are customers who buy really the product for reasons of security, added Pilin.
He said children should always know what is used "the box" and how to use in case of emergency.
The psychologist for children, Dana Bockova, draws the attention that if the child does not want to wear something of this kind on it in débarassera.
"And even the smallest can show great creativity when it comes to get rid of something when they do not want to be under control."
"The phones, which can cut such tracking devices, have already led parents to long expectations," said Bockova.
According to her, the fact that this type of aircraft to assist in case of aggression is highly questionable.
"If it is a whaler prepared, the author will do everything to ensure that the child has no electronic device that can locate."
"Currently, it is the telephone."
"As soon as will develop the tracking devices, they (criminals) will also seek the because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
"In such cases criminals are always ahead of the police," said psychologist.
She confesses that such devices can help during an assault not prepared by a paedophile.
According to Robert Cech of society RC Monitoring, which offers both for cars and for people tracing services, says that to have this type of aircraft can help, even if it is destroyed in the case of an attack.
"The device can be paramétré so that it is issuing regular after a specified period."
"In the case where the device is destroyed, it remains the final position of the person concerned."
"The more expensive devices were also a inclinomètre who noted immediately the position of the person who has slipped and is found in the extended position nothing," says Cech.
According to him the so-called intelligent mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after the formatted with a special prologiciel.
The problem of current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those that the pendentif is the size of a box of matches to smaller telephone equipment.
We can always lose.
According to Pilina of the company Macro Weil, that is why tests are currently conducted to make devices that resemble common digital watches.
"It will have the advantage that any aggressor will not recognize the tracking device."
"Or it will after a certain time, which will have given the police a little more time," he adds.
The tracking device is developed in the form of bracelet or pendentif, the utilisiera always the same technology that to draw cars.
It is a position at the GPS-derived through a combination of acquisition systems (which is commonly used in autonavigation) and a function of a mobile phone to alert the current position of a vehicle.
