The army has therefore reserves for 225 years ago.
The problem is that the life of cordeaux is two to four years.
The army has bought cordeaux détonants Company STV Group for 40 million kroner.
The General Staff has given as a reason for the achât FP's Dnes a huge amount of cordeaux détonants that the soldiers use 60 kilometers per year.
According to the calculations of reserve to hold made by the pyrotechniciens of the army, that FP's Dnes has contacted, it is clear that even the generals, the officers with a command, secretaries or the personal household should have a year to explosives each year.
Alexander Vondra, Minister for Defence and Vlastimil Picek, commander of the army are no exception.
Only to argue the annual consumption of the army of 60 kilometers of cordeaux détonants.
At this distance corresponds 25,000 explosions.
And even if it were true, the army reserves could support themselves for 10 years.
If it is true that for basic training of each new professionals it is enough to more than 2 m cordeaux détonants, as the experts, this means that the army with its new purchase assured - with the use of special units and engineering - reserves for the 225 years ago mentioned.
Yet the soldiers of the rapid intervention brigade have recently complained to the Minister Vondra that they have almost no ammunition for their handguns and the shooting sessions are limited because of the needs of money.
About the lack of linen body is not talking about.
"And I do not take the lead if they buy in such a large quantity of cordeaux détonants."
"And it is their decision and they really know what they are doing."
"For us the military is a good client that we are trying as traders be content," said the commercial director of STV Group Jan Decky.
Jan Pejsek, spokesman of the Ministry of Defence, argues the achât of hundreds of kilometers of cordeaux détonants by the fact that the army will these "munitions" in reserve for 10 years.
Jan Decky of STV Group reported however of cordeaux only four years of life détonants and the pyrotechniciens of the police and the army of only two years.
"If they are perfectly stored in the depots, it can go up to four years," said one which does not want his name published criticism of the army.
The period of life past, each ammunition must be tested to see if it remains integrates and does not threaten the life of the soldier.
These tests are not free and still cost money.
The other argument the department is a discount due to the amount to 445 kilometers of cordeux détonants.
"They have cost 60% less than the provision of the past year of 245 km," says the Pejsek spokesman the interpreter of the opinion of the buyers of the Ministry of Defence.
Just to compare: the annual consumption of détonants pyrotechniciens cordeaux police that neutralize the ammunition of the Second World War or those after the Soviet army, does not exceed 1,500-meter.
And the police order only the quantity of ammunition to be used before the end of their lifetime.
It has been established for pyrotechniciens security reasons and to be able to more flexible more modern and more reliable détonants types of cordeaux.
The Ministry of Defence today has big problems for the neutralization of dozens of tons of ammunition from the time of the Warsaw Pact when the Czechoslovak army of two hundred thousand men preparing to move, Cap.452 on the Rhine.
