Knowing that he was still a student in trosième year of higher education, it was a courageous action.
"The relationship between the quality and the price of accommodation in our region made me want to do something," said Lucas Pytloun.
He began renting the first apartment gravehouses foreign workers.
It reinvests the benefit in the building it transformed into pension with 54 beds.
Since that time, his action contractor allowed him to open Libérec 4 pensions, two restaurants in style and two hotels with a total capacity of nearly 300 beds in all categories of accommodation.
