The investigation which eliminates unreasonable regulations.
The investigation into the Absurdité of the year is for the fourth time part of the business clan.
Some absurd regulations could be removed.
The survey inglorious winner this year on the Absurdité of the year was the obligation to provide in the offices of the documents that employees can get online.
Over one-third of 4,000 voters have voted for it.
For example, the social affairs authorities asked a paper from the register of commerce, while the official can get two mouse clicks.
Change thanks to the investigation.
"The Czech administration of social insurance will ask the extract of the trade register for controls of insurance payments," said Jana Buranova, spokesman for the Czech Administration social insurance (CSSZ).
Highlight all regulations and orders that companies and contractors must meet in Czech Republic and remove those that are absurd is the meaning of this competition for the Absurdité of the year.
This investigation is again this year for the fourth time part of the business clan organized by Hospodarske noviny and has even greater popularity.
If the last year 1,000-3,000 voting occurred, it is at least 4,000 this year who have made their voices heard.
And this is not surprising, there are in our country the various legal obligations that only curb the company, and increasingly.
"We are perhaps the number of documents to fill for the tax returns to the top places in the world," said Karel Havlicek of the Association of small and medium-sized businesses and entrepreneurs in the Czech Republic.
The simplification of entrepreneurial activity becomes a goal proclaimed by all governments in recent years.
In comparison with the world does not improve the situation in the Czech Republic.
According to the World Bank the Czech Republic is the property.74 place as regards the conditions for the company, or 8 seats compared to last year.
The competition for the Absurdité of the year has been put in place for the first time in 2006 and continues each year according to the same scenario.
Anyone can make each year administrative and bureaucratic nonsense in late September, last time before the close of the competition.
To make the website at firmaroku banking. Then, the organiser of the competition selects seven candidates for "the antiprix" and leaves the public vote during the month of October on the site. firmaroku. banking/absurdita and at ihned banking.
The Absurdité who received the greatest number of votes is declared winner.
Until the last survey of the last year, it is a hundred-odd, or more precisely 105 regulations and décrêts who have lost their sense of existence.
The remarks are sent by entrepreneurs but also the professional unions and teachers.
Among the "runner-" of the competition, therefore one of the nominees is for example the requirement that the vehicle maintenance motorways and expressways pay tolls, or that the contractors with 20 employees, paint two offices and two toilets every two years.
The list of seven proposals is published on the website of the competition.
The proclamation of the competition, which begins in early November on the Place Venceslas in Prague, is a part of a 'happening' involving regularly personalities of the public and political life.
This year, for example, Eva Svobodova, director of the Association for small and medium-sized businesses in the Czech Republic or Petr Kuzel, President of the Chamber of Commerce of the Czech Republic, attended the culmination of the competition.
"Economic prosperity cannot function when the state puts âtons in the legs of entrepreneurs and for this my goal is to remove every year, at least three dozen paragraphs that today only complicate the business," said Martin Kocourek, the Minister of Industry and Trade.
The effort to remove the absurd décrêts is not a weapon in the water.
In 2007, which did not appeal to the people was the obligation of entrepreneurs to declare three days before the office for the individual company at the location of the company, the intention to go to an exhibit or pilgrimages with a booth.
This obligation was removed with the ammendement of the Act on the individual enterprise.
The second most popular obligation in 2007, which was to report to the Office of the service a trip for a foreign employee on 30 days, has been removed with the text of Act on what we call the green card.
And everything is okay until the third session of the competition.
The Absurdité of the year 2009 has been the décrêt for physiotherapists have a large mirror in their office, a refrigerator and two automatic balances.
This has been changed by order of the Ministry of Health last year - the obligation to have a refrigerator has been removed.
