Households will pay a surcharge of a hundred Wreaths monthly for housing.
Households will from January pay a surcharge not only for all types of energy but also for water and sanitation, heating supplies and in some places rents will increase also.
The families will therefore from January from their wallets until a hundred Wreaths monthly more than now.
Electricity increases 4.6 percent, gas by almost 2% more expensive, in certain localities you will have to pay up to a tenth of the provision of water and in many places will also be more expensive central heating supplies.
The increase in electricity should be close to households apartment 100 Wreaths anuellement more than at present.
However all suppliers have reduced the price of electricity because of the sensitive development to encourage the production of renewable energy sources, including the photovoltaÏques batteries.
The gas increase moderately but of course when people most need to heat and thus the greater consumption.
We can therefore count a hundred Wreaths.
Although the electricity and gas are increasing in the Czech Republic, the change in the price of central heating differs from city to city.
It is mainly the largest common planning the price increase.
For example, or Hradec Kraloce Pardubice households will pay starting in January for the central heating nearly 50 Wreaths more per month, the families of Libérec pay more than 1,000 Wreaths annually.
For the people of Prague prepares an increase of 9% for water and sanitation for the case where the city is increasing rents infrastructure.
If the rent does not change the Prague will pay a supplement of 6.8 percent.
The price in Prague will be part of the lowest in comparison with the entire country.
In northern Bohemia, where prices are already higher, water and sanitation increase of 7.4 percent.
The price of rent will increase significantly in the 450 thousand lettings from January - at the end of regulation.
For example the ICC Byty society that has Usti nad Labem nearly 2,500 apartments, decided an increase up to 100 percent.
Those who will not agree with the new rent increase will be brought before the courts by society.
Rents regulated that pay people in nearly 300,000 apartments could increase next year of 10 percent.
