The group Fujitsu relocates its subsidiary of Bad Homburg to Frankfurt.
The next year in July, 400 staff will transfer to Astro Park their place of work which is currently at the office building in Mareinbader Place in the region of Bad Homburg.
The Japanese group Fujitsu relocated its branch of Bad Homburg in Frankfurt.
As said Wednesday the giant specializing in the manufacture and maintenance of computers, the next year in July, the place of work of 400 men and women up to now, located on the Marienbader of the city of Bad Homburg, will be transferred to Astro Park, enormous complex of offices located on the street Lyoner Straße Niederrad unit.332 in Frankfurt.
A Fujitsu spokesman said that medium term, the group should consolidate 100 other jobs still scattered so far in the region.
The supply of rental has been extremely attractive. Furthermore, the open area of Astro Park offices to better suited to the way work collaborators.
In Bad Homburg, Fujitsu was just leasee.
The Director General, Bernd Wagner, said: "Frankfurt - Niederrad is for us a crucial location with a remarkable infrastructure."
He says that the connection to the airport is of great importance for a global company like Fujitsu.
The new move of a major company within the region has raised yesterday the joy of the winners and caused the disappointment of the losers.
The head of the economic affairs of the municipality of Frankfurt, Mr. Markus Frank (CDU), said that once again, a "global player" had been won.
It is an "extraordinary profession of faith on instead of implementation."
Fujitsu is appropriate for the city and its implementation is a major boost for Niederrad.
