Result of a joint project of the municipality and a private developer of projects, a new entrance to the city was created between the station and City Hall. It prompted numerous critical, not only because of the impressive development surfaces that once served as parking in part, but also because of the height of buildings.
In 2001, rating and investment consulting company, Feri, the manufacturer of computers for the travel distribution systems, Start Amadeus, and Fujitsu, manufacturer of computers at the time still associated with Siemens, have moved into buildings.
In 2006, The German group of Frankfurt specialized Immobilien - Chancen repurchased buildings occupied by Fujitsu at the same time as the real estate funds Morgan Stanley. A year later, these buildings were resold to Spanish society Falcon Real Estate Investments SA Madridbased.
The group Fujitsu, headquartered in Tokyo sees itself as the world's third largest supplier of computer products.
