The master-distributor glacier Luciano Ferrari is ideal characteristics perfect ice.
Determines not only the good taste, but also the soyeuse flexibility and the right consistency.
However, Luciano not forgotten during the training the icing on the cake for National superstructure and, in general, the south: "The Italian ice is simply the best: and then it still retains a sacred dose of romanticism."
The first step in the manufacturing seems quite simple.
Luciano pays basic ingredients such as milk, cream, to milk powder, sugar and stabilisers in a large blender heat to 85 degrees colder through an electronic program, then immediately to four degrees.
He then opened a valve installed on the machine: it out a white pasteurized cream, foundation for all kinds of ice milk.
The coach is immediately beset by question: is it possible to manufacture ice using only the natural substances without output-stabilising?
How can people unleash the pleasure staff of the experiment?
Luciano warns against being misled by the spirit of the time.
Anyone who does that ice-surveillance "made from natural ingredients," perhaps nevertheless used stabilisers: the more often a natural product, for example the guar seed flour obtained from the guar bean.
It is obviously possible to manufacture ice without using output-stabilising, only sell in a period of 24 hours, otherwise it will collapse and the customer croquera nothing other than the ice pellets.
Some amendments to the basic mass are permitted.
This becomes more exciting with flavourings.
The master Luciano establishes the difference between the ingredients that one acquires in the fruit or sweets of the supermarket.
In addition, there are powder and pasta.
"The suppliers will attempt all of you pass dozens of ingredients flavoured."
"However, you should simply try."
In the revenues of fruit sorbet with sugar and fresh fruit.
In the icecream made from the mass of white base, adding egg becomes a yellow cream and is, when we add cocoa powder, the basis of all possible chocolate desserts.
Now, all the participants during must move to the use of machines to ice.
Luciano invites in time to make four kinds of Glaces: vanilla, chocolate, moka and hazelnuts with or without eggs in the mass basis, with more or less aroma of vanilla or other natural ingredients.
The different kinds of fruit icescapeâ? are also subject to the same experience.
More fragrances, more fruit purée: the point of view of taste, it is not absolutely better.
The ice to hazelnuts does not necessarily the taste of the AM1.5, when it consists largely of hazelnuts.
The ice the kiwi fruit, very popular, is made from the group using more fruit and less water and a little less than output-stabilising.
"Only a balanced mix correctly notes the taste of ice-creams," says Luciano.
The manufacture of ice is an exercise of calculation: if you use fishing purée with a lot of sugar, it is important that the quantity of sugar is reduced in the basic recipe.
A supplement of sugar is necessary for the lemon ice.
Luciano presents a device with which it determines the sugar content of different types of fruit (the ice-wine is used to measure the degree of Oechsle in the grape must).
Fortunately, the tables facilitate calculations.
The manufacture of ice no longer requires, as in the past, as much physical intervention.
This is not only the automatic machine manufacturing base mass support.
There is also a device in which it beats simultaneously the mixture of ice available to make it onctueux and reduced to negative temperatures.
In spite of all the automatisations, small fault-monitoring are not excluded.
The Brazilian Gustavo barbouille of fruit purée head to toe, éclabousse comrades studies when the control of the huge bowl blender escapes.
The master Luciano is of the opinion that a "J0 incident to happen in each: it is only a matter of time."
