An opinion indicates that it operates all data, including those in the industry as long as they are of good quality work.
It does not prohibit experts working for the account of the Efsa to forge contacts with this sector of activity.
But they should make them public.
Mr. Kuiper admits that he works for the International Institute for the life sciences (International Life Sciences Institute, Ilsi) based in the United States.
This organization sees itself as a neutral forum bringing together experts who belong, among others, in the field of science, industry and policy in order to assess the risks of biotechnology without being in the pay of a lobby.
In this case, the independent experts such as Mr. Then resent the fact that the genetically modified are accepted without any testing of food animals and that it has not tested the impact of these plants on the environment.
"We want to know what are, for example, the impact of corn genetically modified cause the scope," says Mr. Then.
The current practice is to test only the proteins isolated and not all the GM plant, which does not obtain reliable results.
"If we do not research risks, how can we discover?" asked Mr. Then on an accusatory tone.
It is also the point of view of Ms. Angelika Hilbeck.
This scientific researches since 1994 in the field of genetics and is currently working on the school Polythenique of Zurich.
