Is it Splatter the film artificial?
The director Nicolas Winding Refn explores the limits of such former thanks to his film, "Valhalla Rising" saga of veteran.
How public the Danish director Nicolas Winding Refn has it been thinking in turning point "Valhalla Rising"?
A Viking warrior (Mads Mikkelsen) with only one eye is prisoner; it unloads its hangman and, with an almost supernatural force, eliminate its opponents after each other. It seems ideal for young male viewers in search of a bloody action, precisely because our hero uses of the brutal methods of assassination. when it is bad moods, it severs the gut of its enemies without waiting until they are dead.
On the other hand, until the end of the film, the one-eyed says no word on his real name. Even the other characters leave escape, at most, one or two sentences in side-trip a few cries of agony appalling.
Otherwise, there is nothing and festoie in the mountainous incredibly beautiful landscape of Scotland which is the scene of the universe of Vikings, there are about a thousand years.
This would be ideal more mature filmmakers with an interest in the existentialisme and for the excellent travellings.
When a film is several target groups, it is unfortunate that they are mutually exclusive.
The director Winding Refn is considered, since the release of "Pusher," his trilogy on fierce drug trafficker and full of style, as a kind of Danish Quentin Tarantinon, but it refuses to make a little more mood in the mainstream or introduce a little less brutality of art and testing in cinema.
Most supporters of cinema art to experience horror in the brain that is spreading around and intestines.
Fans of action films die of boredom, when the one-eyed departed, for reasons that can be freely interpret, with a group of Christian missionaries violent in a vessel destined to Jerusalem; they are drowned during an eternity by the calm and the fog before the crew arrives in America and continues to be quiet.
It is not so surprising that "Valhalla Rising" has found no distributor of films in Germany and that there are only in the DVD format.
It is mainly because of the beautiful images of the misery that has earned some attention, but also because the image of an exciting film, occasionally, hiding behind a bloody and over-the-top appearance.
It is not dialogues in this film, or a coherent action, everything is atmosphere, a feverish dream transformed into film.
The viewer cannot escape.
Refn gives just a moment of relaxation and stumping slowly throat with freezing images and a grim soundtrack, but especially with an elusive hatred that comes from the heart of the characters.
Only a young boy, held faithfully alongside the one-eyed, preserves a certain innocence, all the others are managerled anger.
More than anything, the one-eyed heroes that the mobile never are known, but returned to hell at any time to fight enemies and temporarily allied themselves in warrior, may be sent by the devil himself.
It represents the decay, but perhaps also, just for those who are, in any case, rotten.
"Valhalla Rising" is a mysterious film that you can hate and admire, which was intended the agitation, enthusiasm and surprise.
