Zapatero and the German red line
Berlin has opted to remain in the euro, but he sets the conditions for the entire Union.
Market tensions have caused a government response doble.
On the other hand, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero announced new methods of adjustment, which vary from tax reductions for SMEs, regulation of the private placement or removal of 426 euros of aid to the unemployed professional contribution to the privatisation of 49% of AENA, the management of airports Barajas and El Prat and 30% of state Loteries.
Another, the Vice-President Elena Salgado, with the support of the former president Felipe González, unites the criticism of Chancellor Angela Merkel in relation to its responsibility to detach the current crisis.
How are we to interpret these movements?
It should be mentioned that the position of Merkel is not a mistake in its policy communicative.
On the contrary, it is a further restriction of the difficult process of redefinition of the euro.
And here Germany has a radically new vision of what should be its future, which angered with maintaining the old traditions of most of its partners.
The European resistance, Germany begins to speculate on the three possible outflow of the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, integrated by itself, Austria and Holland, among other countries, and the southern abandon the currency area.
The second, the recovery of Mark, even if now it seems science fiction, with a current of opinion very favourable, almost a 50% of the population.
The third, a new design of the euro, in line with the German proposals for greater macroeconomic control, budgetary rigour, fines on countries which, possible suspension of payments violate them and extension to the private sector costs of potential adjustments.
The German position is clear and so long as it is, therefore, now there is no room for excuses.
First, in 2009, when both IMF as the European Commission technique deficits, the German Government has invented constitutional reform to prevent from 2016.
This was the first signal of divergence between what Germany thought that we had to do (plans for fiscal rigour and stability of public finances) and that its European partners, ci- includes France, practised.
The second centre-européen of the country kicked when Merkel has hardly extended the decision to save Greece.
From this time she has been the subject of a fierce critic, but the truth is that the political consensus in Germany and the public opinion and the published were against the rescue of Greece.
Finally, towards the end of October, Merkel expressed again a clear position, in calling for the reform of the EU treaties to make possible the rescue of a country and force 28 private lenders to bear a share of the cost.
This position has been interpreted as anti-European because it precipitated the Irish crisis and the rest.
But his proposal, although slightly watered down, has been approved and, the following month, we should attend the process of reform of the EU to possible these measures from 2013.
Germany drew a red line that it does not cross.
And she said all that, even though now we must take measures with which it may not be too agree, from this date there former functioning of the euro would be finished.
2013 will mean the birth of a new monetary zone, in which the countries which contravene the rules will be severely punished, they may be forced to said termination payments and, in this case, the private sector also bear a party costs.
Germany says that we must follow a strict path of growth with high rates of savings and investment, moderation in consumption, improvements in the productivity and competitiveness and external balances.
An alternative based on the debt and construction, with huge holes in the balance of payments, such as the one who has chaired the Spanish growth in the boom years, will simply not be tolerated.
The development is clear.
And it would be wrong to not hear.
It is not only to renew the public deficit to 3% in 2013.
What we demand is much harder.
And what it must not do in these circumstances is to fool ourselves.
I hope that the current turbulence leave happen to us greater peace.
And that we know to take the opportunity that we have been given until spring of 2013.
It appears that President Zapatero has also heard of this form and his double statement (the reforms promised after the meeting of the past Saturday with large companies and the announcement yesterday of the new measures) suggests that, despite the criticism of Merkel, it has opened the way for the thesis that there must be of the order in the home.
But the red line that Germany has mapped out is there, and they do not seem to move.
And among the possibilities that considering, we cannot exclude that to abandon a monetary area loaded with too few serious countries.
And in this case, Germany we can always say that we had been warned.
Sport and the law fraud
The tricks similar to that of Alonso and Ramos against Ajax show ingenuity but not the desire to escape a sanction.
EVICTION played in principle by two players from Real Madrid (Xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) during the match on 23 November against Ajax in the Champions League has caused much ink on the sports nature of such behaviour and if the two players should be sanctioned by UEFA.
As you know, a few minutes before finishing the game RARELY (that their team clearly), the two players have deliberately lost the time when they have committed mistakes to determine the referee to show them the second yellow card.
Thus, and given that Real Madrid will be leader of his group, the two players make regulatory enforcement during the next game of the dam match against Auxerre and can pass without paperboards to the next phase.
Finally, the UEFA disciplinary committee has punished the coach of the team with two games, José Mourinho and various are economic players involved.
The provocation of a yellow card in such or similar circumstances is not a new practice, otherwise rather frequent in the world of football.
It is so widespread that it is party of the ethos, written rules, but followed, this sport.
Part of the debate emerged in the case related to the fact that this has had a team of the entity as protagonist's Real Madrid (which in its anthem poster the nobility and honor and which in the past occasions was fined its players for similar acts) and to the dramatization orchestrated, it seems, by Mourinho, which adds an episode of history inflated histrionique technician and provocative.
In any case, the debate whether this type of behaviour not specifically by the regulation contradicts the principles of sport, that is, if with these actions is a fraud law, because, in effect, they are respectful actions with the sporting regulations, but seem to evade its meaning.
The question is to examine the type of damage they cause to the sporting spirit.
A property that includes the sporting spirit is the physical integrity of opposing players, something that with these actions has not been endangers, i.e. there has not been a violent game.
Another of those goods which refers to the proper game is avoid the team players offenders enjoys an unfair way contrary to the team, which is not the case.
However, the action of players from the Real Madrid paradox is that it does not accept what is normally characterized as cheating o fraud of the law, because its violation of the rules has not been carried out in secret to try to avoid the penalty, but their action has specifically tried to be the most obvious possible to receive the criminalization of the arbitrator.
They were waiting and they have accepted the sanction.
Another issue is the type of advantage that the offenders get errors well-intentioned examined.
Here it seems necessary to see that we are not in a situation of disadvantage to rival and does an advantage in the same game either, because obviously the result of the action involves the letting their own team with fewer players.
And this is not a useful strategy for the next game either, because the club could not rely on these players.
Of course the advantage lies in the fact that the players will begin the next phase of the Champions League without cardboards that could threaten their participation in a future game.
But this is a long-term benefit, with a degree of ambiguity, because the team could be eliminated all of a sudden and otherwise, with this action the players perform a match penalty and spend in the second round of paperboards, in which the suspension due to the accumulation of cardboards occurs with a less than in the first round.
So, climb the ladder, this is not so clear that this is an advantage.
Ultimately, these actions are not contrary to the sporting spirit, which is still part of strategic decisions that promote the advantage of what the rules allow.
In our case, the players were not activated to avoid the application of the sanction (this would be a clear cases of fraud the law), m otherwise they have chosen the time in which they are subject to it.
They have taken a strategic decision without defeat the penalty or flee this.
Even if the border between engineering and fraud of the law is diffuse, on this occasion I think that there has been a clear case of engineering.
The controversy, it seems to me, seems due to two factors: because there were two self Deportations and because of the way to convey the Director for the cause.
The harm caused to the principles of sport by these actions is not as much ethical as aesthetic.
