The 20 police international headquarters in Lyon (France) has driven the demand of Sweden, but it has not made public until yesterday, after having received permission from the authorities of this country.
Thus, the 188 countries of Interpol received indication to identify or locate Assange "for provisionnelle arrest and extradition."
Although UN-organ may not give the order to arrest of a person affected by a red alert, many among the member countries, according to the explanations of the organization, consider the appeal red notice a way for the arrest - that the national police corps must achieve, especially if they have a bilateral extradition agreement, as is the case of Sweden and England, where you think that Assange is.
The movement has outraged lawyers to Assange, who yesterday published a letter dénonceant the fact that the founder of Wikileaks, 39, has shown by video conference to answer questions from the Swedish authorities.
