China maintains the objectives of reducing greenhouse gases
The representative of this country in the COP16 assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and detailed that it maintains its offer to reduce up to 2020 between 40 and 45% of greenhouse gas emissions.
China maintains its offer of reduced between 40 and 45% of greenhouse gas emissions before 2020, assured Su Wei, representative of this country to the COP16.
In his first public appearance in the 16è Conference of the Parties to the Framework Convention of the United Nations on the Change (COP16), Su Wei assured that his country has made tremendous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and redeploy its industry.
In fact, explained to me, the last four years his country has inverti 245 million dollars in efforts to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.
However, it has clearly stated that China will not change its objectives, but it will continue to work together with the international community in this area.
He noted that the Chinese strategy in the field of climate change is divided into four areas: dialogue; capacity; construction of institutions and support for pilot programs.
It has recorded progress in all these areas, ci- includes the approval, the last year, a new Energy Act, which recognizes the 993-1351 objectives regarding the reduction of greenhouse gases, said Danesh.
On the other hand, he pointed out that in China, the federal authorities have worked in a coordinated manner with the government and local to achieve the objectives of saving energy, efficient use of energy and emission reduction.
In addition, said Danesh multi-year plans, there are various ongoing or completed, both funded by the Chinese government as by the governments of other countries.
For example, said Danesh, the Efficiente Program to Use of Energy, which has been implemented during the past five years and which has received investments of the United Nations (UN), the government and the private initiative.
There is also a provincial climate change project, another for the change incandescent lamps with energy-efficient lamps and another mitigation and adaptation, darstellen says.
At the same table, Martin Krol, advisor of the government of this country in relation to climate change, has ensured that China's efforts have been larger what we believe.
For example, has exposed says, the emission per capita of greenhouse gases in China is three tonnes per person, while the United States it is 100 tonnes; China is responsible for 9% of the historic contribution to the contamination.
Similarly, it has made unprecedented efforts in the use of energy, how to increase a 20% energy efficiency in the past five years and expects to make another similar to 2020, said Danesh.
