With the duel of Santos Laguna, Monterrey in the final, there are two different styles competing, marked by their technicians, who find a sharp contrast between them by the results.
Rubén Omar Romano had three defeats in the final, it has had ups and downs in his career, but he has managed to achieve three times the decisive series, although so far it has not put in the mile and that is why this opportunity is very special for him.
The Argentine eventually console themselves with the medal of Deputy champion, he remained a step behind the winners and Notch-1 with the same team he has played consecutive finals.
The strategist's santiste came to his first final as a coach in the Opening Tournament 2002, when he was keen the reins of Morelia with which it has lost with an overall score of 4 - 2 against; later, in the 2003 Clôture also arrived at the decisive duel and lost again with the overall result of 3 - 1 and it was precisely against Rayados.
