14 alleged drug traffickers arrested
A dozen searches were carried out in economy.?, Wednesday, in the framework of the dismantling of a network of production and sale of cannabis.
Fourteen people were arrested and will face various charges.
The searches took place in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, predominantly in places that would have been used in the production of drugs.
"Approximately 750 cannabis plants, four kilograms of hashish, money and equipment used to production have been seized," said Louis-Philippe Ruel, spokesperson of the Sûreté du Québec.
In all, 11 men and three women have been arrested, including the two leaders alleged, two men from Sherbrooke this network.
Those arrested had to appear in court on Sherbrooke in the hours after their arrest.
They could face charges of production of cannabis, possession for the purpose of trafficking, conspiracy and theft of services, among others.
These searches took place in the wake of a lengthy investigation, which lasted nearly a year.
"This is the information received from the public which enabled us to make these arrests," said Mr. Ruel.
Some 70 police officers of the regional survey module of the economy.? of the Sûreté du Québec, the Sherbrooke Police Service and police Régie's Memphrémagog, took part in this police operation.
