At the beginning of 2005, the consortium Energyand stewarship here won the lucrative contract without that there has been a public tender.
For the Parti Quebecois, the use of business consortia poses a serious ethical problem that threatens to eliminate competition and cause a rise in prices.
"This is the new way of making the collusion and break down the competition."
"That the people, instead of making secret that now are open," said yesterday the Member péquiste Sylvain Simard in a press conference.
