"If you go in tender and that there was little bidders, assured. prices will be higher."
"You have two choices: either that you take people who are in the world--that market and that you say: we will negotiate a satisfactory agreement and with a good price."
"But the idea is that this is not the price that is important, it is the competence of the people," said Mr. Laporte.
The contract awarded to the consortium Energyand stewarship is part of a long list of contracts over $50,000 obtained by the Parti Québécois.
The contracts were awarded by Hydro-Québec/SEBJ for the project Eastmain 1 - A- Sarcelle - Rupert.
