Revenge hackers and spies diligence
The case Wikileaks has a dual value.
One hand, it is an apparent scandal, one that is as scandal before the hypocrisy which governs the relationship between the states, the citizens and the press.
On the other, it announces changes at international level, and foreshadows a future dominated by the regression.
But £15,000 order.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks, this is confirmation of the fact that each file by a secret service (of whatever nation) is composed exclusively of press clippings.
The "extraordinary" gratae.13 US on sexual habits of Berlusconi only on Science-driven who for months could be read in any newspaper (except those which Berlusconi owns), and the profile eerily caricature of Gaddafi was long for the artists cabaret skit.
The rule according to which the secret files should be composed of new already known is essential to the dynamic of the secret services, and not only in this century.
If you go into a bookshop on esoteric publications, you will see that each book repeat (on the Holy Grail, the mystery of Rennes-le-Château, Templiers or Rose-Croix) exactly what was already written in previous books.
And not only because the author of dark texts do not like to unpublished research (and does not know where to look for news on the non-existent), but because those involved in the alchemy does not believe that what they know already, and that confirm what they had already learned.
It is the mechanism of the success of Dan Brown.
Ditto for the secret files.
The content-provider's is lazy, lazy (or spirit limited) the head of the secret services (otherwise it could be, whatever, editor of Libération), which is as true that what he acknowledges.
The top secret information on Berlusconi that the US Embassy in Rome sent to the Department of State were the same as those that Newsweek magazine ran the week before.
So why the revelations on these issues have so much noise?
For one, they say that any person cultivated is already known, namely that the embassies, at least since the end of the Second World War, and since the Heads of State can call or take a plane to meet for dinner, have lost their diplomatic service and, except for some small exercises of representation, turned into centres of espionage.
Any investigative film viewer knows this, and it is only by hypocrisy that are pretending to ignore.
However, the repeat publicly violates the duty of hypocrisy, and serves to put in a bad light American diplomacy.
Secondly, the idea that any hacker can capture the most secret secrets of the world's most powerful country deals a significant blow to the prestige of the Department of State.
The scandal does not crisis victims that the "5401B."
But let us move on to the nature of what happened.
Once, at the time of Orwell, you could design power as a Big Brother, which controlled every gesture of his subjects.
The Orwellian prophecy was completely stage6 since, that can monitor each movement through the phone, every transaction, the hotel visited, Highway borrowed and following the citizen became the victim of the eye of power.
But when it shows, as it happens now, that even the cryptes of the secrets of power cannot escape the control ceases to be a hacker one-way and becomes circular.
The control every citizen, but every citizen, or at least the hacker - elected as vengeful citizen - can know all the secrets of power.
How a power that no longer has the opportunity to maintain its own secret can take?
It is true, Georg Simmel said already, that a true secret is a secret vacuum (and secret vacuum will never be disclosed); it is true, too, that all know about the character of Berlusconi or Merkel is actually a secret empty of secrecy, because falling within the public domain; but reveal, as did WikiLeaks, that the secrets of Hillary Clinton were empty secrets means remove any power.
WikiLeaks did no harm to Sarkozy and Merkel, but in fact a too large to Clinton and Obama.
What are the consequences of this injury inflicted on a very powerful?
In the future, it is clear that states can no longer be in line no information - this would be tantamount to publish on a poster hung at the corner of the street.
But it is also obvious that with the current technologies, it is pointless to hope to be able to maintain the confidential reports by telephone.
Nothing easier than to find out if and when a head of state has moved aircraft and contacted one of his colleagues.
How can be maintained in the future the reserved and private reports?
I know that, for the moment, my forecast therefore is science fiction and novels, but I am obliged to conceive of government agents who move quietly in coaches uncontrollable routes, as did growthgenerating that messages learned by heart, or at most, by hiding the few written information in the heel of a shoe.
The information will be stored in single copy in drawers locked: basically, the Watergate espionage attempt has been less successful than WikiLeaks.
I had the opportunity to write that technology now advance in crab, i.e. backwards.
A century after the wireless telegraph revolutionized communications, the Internet has restored a telegraph on son (telephone).
The L'énergie (analog) had allowed researchers film to explore a film not going forward and backwards and in discovering all the secrets of the assembly, whereas now CDs (digital) do that to jump to chapter, i.e. macroportions.
With high-speed trains, we are going to Rome to Milan in three hours, then that plane, and travel that it includes, it takes three hours and a half.
It is therefore not extraordinary that the political and the technical communications from horseback cars.
A final observation.
Once, the press tried to understand what was going on in the secrecy of embassies.
Now, this is the embassies seeking confidential information to the press.
Climate: how France bidouille its promises of funding
A year after the Copenhagen Agreement, it is time to examine the respect of the promises of funding quickly released (Aeranautical fast start or early funding) made by the developed countries.
And the big French bidouillages are revealed.
In the Copenhagen agreement, developed countries are committed to providing $30 billion between 2010 and 2012.
The European Union has pledged 7.2 billion euros over three years and France 1.26 billion euros (420 million per year).
At the opening of the COP16, the EU took the adesso to persuade its partners of the reality of its commitment regarding the funding fast start: report detailing the activities of its Member States, press conference, large side event, distribution of leaflets...
The operation transparency is appreciable and appreciated at its right value: developing countries and civil society would like that all developed countries to do the same with the same level of precision.
The EU announcement have reached in 2010 2.2 billion euros, which puts on the right path for the respect of his commitment of $7.2 billion in 2012.
But when we look at in detail, things are more complicated.
This money should be, according to the Copenhagen agreement, "new and additional," in order to ensure that an additional effort is made without being at the expense of Official Development Assistance.
Unfortunately, there is no agreement on what "new and additional" means.
While the European Commission had proposed a harmonization, some member states including France have blocked the procedure.
Today, everyone chooses the reference that is best.
The European Commission has for example seen as reference year 2009: the international funding are maintained, and she adds $150 million over three years under funding fast start.
Other countries have chosen similar references in terms of year or in terms of the level of public development aid.
In contrast, France believes that the financing of "all new projects" of the year 2010 are "new and additional."
In other words, there is no reference to previous years' expenditures or the overall level of official development assistance.
Specifically, the total amount of the support of France for developing countries can remain stable (or even diminish), it claims to respect its commitment to "new and additional funding..."
Another crucial element, the division between donations and loans.
Again, there is no rule and everyone chooses its method of calculation.
Some, such as France, consider that 1 lent equivalent to 1.
Of course, this is hardly justifiable: the effort is not comparable.
If the use of loans can be justified for certain investments which are profitable (often projects related to the mitigation of emissions that are based on more effective technologies), it is misleading to present a euro that we will recover as equivalent to a euro that it gives... at most, should be counted in respect of its commitments that the cost of the loan for the country lender (or the equivalent of an interest rate).
But France has such reasoning: it "respects" its commitment of EUR 420 million by making 91.5% of loans (389,8 million euros) and 8.5% of donations (36.1 million euros) - see the document of the EU to check yourself.
It is the only country in the European Union to use if massively the loan.
Germany requires to 46%, while Denmark, the Netherlands or Slovakia (other) respect their commitments with 100 percent of donations.
In other words, when the vast majority of the European Union puts 1 to meet its commitment, France does that 10 cents and considers that the effort is comparable.
Nice sleight of hand!
In summary, in its funding fast start, France operates a double anti-rackets: one on the evolution of the action in the time and on the reality of the financial effort.
By spending only 36.1 million euros, it happens to make believe that spends $420 million "new and additional" consistent with its promises.
The manipulation of the Department of Finance (because it appears that it is Bercy who has made arbitration) could have a double negative impact, both within the EU (why the other Member States would continue to give if it is enough to lend?) and in the negotiations since developing countries are not completely fooled...
The chapter of early funding is a small matter, on short term, compared to the whole discussion on the climate.
But it could be a grain of sand in the huge machine that is the conflict.35.
Let us hope that this will not be the case.
Regardless, it is essential to learn the lessons of this first year of early funding.
First, France could announce a change in its method of accounting for the years 2011 and 2012, in a spirit of respect of its commitments and equity with other countries of the European Union.
But above all, France could advance discussions on the issues of long-term funding (another crucial chapter currently discussed): you will not escape the question of "additionality" or the way of accounting for loans.
France could change its position to become as progressive on these issues that it is on others.
The hope is based on the new Minister of the Environment, Mrs Kosciusko-Morizet, which will arrive in Cancun next week.
A surprise announcement on the fast start of France and its vision of "additionality" and the use of loans would increase the level of international confidence necessary to make progress in the discussions.
Alert to pesticides ingested by children
A child of 10 years interfering in different81 chemicals a day, according to a study published Wednesday in the association Generations Futures (ex-public Movement for Rights and the respect of future generations).
The association, which warned that its results "were not significant statistical value in the light of the low number of samples analyzed, but are illustrative of the problem dealt with," has purchased between July and September foods usually consumed in four meals and a snack in one day by a child, in the Oise Vangyard a dozen years and Paris.
These meals types, including the official recommendations - five fruits and vegetables, three dairy and 1.5 litre of water per day - as well as sweets, have been examined by laboratories in search of chemicals, pesticides, heavy metals and other pollutants.
The balance sheet of the base is overwhelming: 81 chemicals which 42 are probable or possible carcinogens and five substances are carcinogenic some and 37 likely to act as endocrine disruptors (EP), according to studies by several institutions such as the International Centre for Research on Cancer.
"Even if, in almost all cases, the legal limits for each chemical taken individually are not exceeded, we can see in our investigation that the reality of consumer exposure to contaminants possibly carcinogenic and/or EP is worrying," notes the association.
For breakfast, butter and milk tea alone contain more than a dozen possible carcinogenic residues and three proven as some 2000xxiv and nearly twenty residues likely to disrupt the hormonal system.
Apple, imported from Brazil, planned as a snack by the study, presents traces of six chemicals that PKPB1 still banned in France.
Same thing for the green beans from Kenya, included in the luncheon, on which the study has detected traces of a powerful insecticide banned in the EU.
In addition, the steak chopped, canned tuna, and even the loaves of bread and chewing gum were full of pesticides and other chemicals.
In the tap water analyses have revealed the presence of nitrates and chloroform.
For dinner, the salmon steak was the most "rich" with 34 woodresidue chemicals detected and even the review of the plastic base used to warm the meal in the microwave was not free.
The risk final for the consumer of this "cocktails of contaminants" is probably underestimated ," according to the study.
Europe earthquake-resistant Alliance - The Greens (EE, LV), for its part, has proposed "faced with the urgency of the situation" to establish a moratorium on the use of pesticides, in order to stop "the increase in diseases of civilisation."
In July, a European Food Safety Agency (EFSA) study of the reported the presence of residues of various pesticides 365 identified in fruits and vegetables consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
